!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

historical /hɪˈstɒrɪkəl/

1. ADJ Historical people, situations, or things existed in the past and are considered to be a part of history. 历史上的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...an important historical figure. …一位重要的历史人物。 

例： ...the historical impact of Western capitalism on the world. …西方资本主义对全世界的历史影响。 

2. historically ADV 在历史上 

例： Historically, royal marriages have been cold, calculating affairs. 从历史上来看，王室婚姻一直都是冷酷、精心策划的结合。 

3. ADJ Historical books, movies, or pictures describe or represent people, situations, or things that existed in the past. 历史题材的 [ADJ n] 

例： He is writing a historical novel about nineteenth-century France. 他正在写一部关于19世纪的法国的历史小说。 

4. ADJ Historical information, research, and discussion is related to the study of history. 史学的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...historical records. …史学记录。

</div>

